---
@version: [current]
@description: Store alert message to session.
@lot: string $type, string $message, array $vars, bool $preserve_case = false
@example: |
  Alert::set('error', 'Error message here.');
...

The engine will first search for an `alert-{$type}-* language property that has the same suffix as the message text and return that property value:

~~~ .php
// Search for `$language->alertTestSuccess`, otherwise return `success`
Alert::set('test', 'success');
~~~